  {
    "page_number": 3,
    "bbox": [
      115.54,
      88.13,
      318.89,
      187.94
    ],
    "text": "Happy Wanderer I love to go a-wandering, Along the mountain track, And as I go, I love to sing, My knapsack on my back.",
    "fonts": [
      "Apple-Chancery"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      13.0,
      15.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 3,
    "bbox": [
      115.54,
      193.93,
      258.02,
      275.94
    ],
    "text": "Chorus: Val-deri,Val-deraVal-deri,Val-dera-ha-ha-ha-ha-ha Val-deri,Val-dera.",
    "fonts": [
      "Apple-Chancery"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      13.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 3,
    "bbox": [
      115.54,
      279.93,
      281.89,
      361.93
    ],
    "text": "My knapsack on my back.I love to wander by the stream That dances in the sun, So joyously it calls to me, \"Come! Join my happy song!\"",
    "fonts": [
      "Apple-Chancery"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      13.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 3,
    "bbox": [
      115.54,
      367.92,
      317.95,
      449.93
    ],
    "text": "Chorus: I wave my hat to all I meet, And they wave back to me, And blackbirds call so loud and sweet From ev'ry green wood tree.",
    "fonts": [
      "Apple-Chancery"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      13.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 3,
    "bbox": [
      115.54,
      451.93,
      299.5,
      533.93
    ],
    "text": "Chorus: High overhead, the skylarks wing, They never rest at home But just like me, they love to sing, As o'er the world we roam.",
    "fonts": [
      "Apple-Chancery"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      13.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 3,
    "bbox": [
      115.54,
      537.93,
      301.52,
      619.93
    ],
    "text": "Chorus: Oh, may I go a-wandering Until the day I die! Oh, may I always laugh and sing, Beneath God's clear blue sky!",
    "fonts": [
      "Apple-Chancery"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      13.0
    ]
  },
